<br>
In simple terms there is a real shortage of mid/high end gear flowing around in the economy.  The biggest reason for this?  No-Drop items proliferate the game.  In the beginning there was a real need for this.  There was no way to distinguish between level 1 twinks and level 50, and later 60, players.<br>
<br>
Our current dev's have solved this problem, there are level restrictions now in existence and in place on the majority of PoP loot.  This is excellent and needs to be applied to older no-drop gear.  For example, almost everything from ToV was no drop, why does this need to be the case anymore.  Why cant I give my old Barrier of Sound that is rotting in my bank to a guildmate who has something worse.  It should have a required level of 55 and then he has a new item that I had rotting.  Alternatively I could sell the item, again if the guild doesn't object...why shouldn't I be able to.  In either case everyone goes away happy.<br>
<br>
This change would stimulate the economy of EQ.  It would give a real boost, although short lived, to the activity in the economy.  But the long range effect would be a more diverse and intriguing economy.  Rarely these days do I see people who specialize in the economy of EQ.  Through the Kunark era, I knew individuals who made playing the marketplace thier number one occupation.  They are all gone now, partly as the effect of the Bazaar made it painless to take the time to sell, but moreover as a result of a stagnated economy that is still dealing with a Fungi Tunic from Kunark as one of the top end items in the regular economy.<br>
<br>
My proposed solution follows:<br>
<br>
No-Drop non quest items have a required level that is set by the following chart.<br>
<br>
Average Level of MOB in zone / Required Level<br>
<br>
10 / 5<br>
<br>
20 / 10<br>
<br>
30 / 15<br>
<br>
35 / 20<br>
<br>
40 / 30<br>
<br>
50 / 35<br>
<br>
55 / 40<br>
<br>
60 / 45 and up<br>
<br>
65 / 50 and up<br>
<br>
You will notice a bigger jump from 35 / 20 to 40 / 30, this is to acknowledge that most of the real twinking gear comes from the 40 and up zones.  If you are 30 hunting in 40ish zones then that seems reasonable as your hunting on average things 10 levels higher than you.<br>
<br>
I beseech the dev team to take the time and implement a retro No-Drop change to level restrictions. <p><hr>
